<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="447" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,289,929]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,796,821]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">Remarks.</emphasis>
The unique antennal sensilla suggest that coeloconic sensilla can be transformed into supernumerary basiconic sensilla, as appears to happen in some Aphrophorinae. However, these are not just abnormally formed sensilla, as their arrangement on the postpedicel also differs significantly from those of the sister-species, described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
